</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-366_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-368_">What is World Day for Safety and Health at Work?
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/What_is_World_Day_for_Safety_and_Health_at_Work_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_-_1.png?v=1682524760" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/What_is_World_Day_for_Safety_and_Health_at_Work_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_-_1.png?v=1682524760 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/What_is_World_Day_for_Safety_and_Health_at_Work_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_-_1_500x.png?v=1682524760 320w" width="1244" height="829" alt="What is World Day for Safety and Health at Work? - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " title="What is World Day for Safety and Health at Work? - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-369_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-370_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-372_">World Day for Safety and Health at Work is celebrated each year on the 28th of April. It was initiated to raise awareness, promote and discuss the importance of a safe and healthy work environment.
<br><br>Observing World Day since 2003 has been the International Labour Organisation's way of harmonising its tripartism and social dialogue traditions. It also emphasises the prevention of accidents and diseases at work.
<br>
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-373_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-375_">What is the theme for this year?
